<b><font size="3"><a name="10">General Guild Direction</a></b>:</font><br><br>
<FONT class=Courier10 face="Courier New, adobe-courier, Courier" size=2>
We are a raiding guild. We will raid raid nearly every night (in some form) from 7pm EST to 2am EST and from 1pm EST to 3am EST on the weekends or later.</FONT><br>

<br><hr align="CENTER" size="2" width="80%" noshade><br>

<p><font size=3><b><a name="20">Guild Charter</a></b>:</font></p>

<p><FONT class=Courier10 face="Courier New, adobe-courier, Courier" size=2>In order to face the challenges provided in the game of Everquest, players must band together in order to succeed. To this end, the guild is the means to facilitate the teamwork necessary to succeed. Fury's Edge is a raiding guild, banded together to tackle the toughest challenges Everquest has to offer, both current and future and to allow its members the oppurtunity to participate in the extraordinary encounters and the extremely difficult tasks that can only be accomplished by the elite.</p>

<p>Fury's Edge is guided by three principles: Friendship, Respect, and Desire. Each of these things is vital for a successful and thriving guild. Friendship is important because at the bottom of it all, Everquest is about having fun, and being with friends is enjoyable. Respect is a fundamental aspect of our guild, both to our own members, and to the other members of the Morell-Thule community. Desire is necessary to ensure that we need our goals.</p>

<p>Fury's Edge is the combination of two previous rivals with the desire to bring together the best players on Morell-Thule.</p>

<br><hr align="CENTER" size="2" width="80%" noshade><br>

<p><font size="3"><b><a name="30">Leadership Structure</a></b>:</font></p>

<FONT class=Courier10 face="Courier New, adobe-courier, Courier" size=2>
Guild Leaders: Daggen / Solthan<br>
General Duties: Guild Relations, Officer management, Disciplinary Actions, General guild direction<br><br>

Raid Officers: Daggen / Solthan/Open<br>
General Duties: Scheduling Raids, Groups, Strategies, Assigns and Debriefs trainers<br><br>

Recruiting / HR Officers: Cannabulon<br>
General Duties: Determine needed recruits, conduct reviews, maintain officer and private app forum updates. <br><br>

Loot/Points Officer: Xazy/Jakke<br>
General Duties: Points accounting<br><br>

Vault Officer: Neuro<br>
General Duties: Hold vaulted material, conduct auctions, monthly updated vault status, responsible for providing raid material (gems, Potions, et al).<br><br>

Policies Admin / PR Officer: Open<br>
General Duties: General upkeep of polices, general upkeep of information lists, equipment, etc.<br><br>

Web Master : Draekk<br>
General Duties: Web Page upkeep<br><br>
</font>

<br><hr align="CENTER" size="2" width="80%" noshade><br>

<b><font size="3"><p><a name="40">Member Guidelines</a></b>:</font></p>

<b><font size="3"><a name="41">General</a></b>:</font><br>
<FONT class=Courier10 face="Courier New, adobe-courier, Courier" size=2>
<p>Always, always, always remember this - even if you dont take anything away from your time with Fury's Edge, always remember...that thornybriar has a tiny wang.  That is all :)</p>



<b><font size="3"><a name="42">Guild Tag</a></b>:</font><br>
<FONT class=Courier10 face="Courier New, adobe-courier, Courier" size=2>
<p>When you plan to de-guilding yourself, talk to an officer first. Do not play around with you guild tag lightly! If you do de-guild and want back in, you will have to reapply. Do not let people outside Fury's Edge play your characters with the guild tag without your supervision*. If you are not absolutely certain, that these people are not members of another Morell Thule guild please /guildremove yourself before letting your friends who aren't in Fury's Edge play your character .</p>

<p>* if you have family members taking over your character for a while, or you have friends over at your house etc.</p></font>

<b><font size="3"><a name="43">Common Sense</a></b>:</font><br>
<FONT class=Courier10 face="Courier New, adobe-courier, Courier" size=2>
<p>Now we do need a little common sense. I refuse to let this system be broken down by someone trying to exploit some flaw in it. In some cases these rules will be bent. Remember this is new to us but we do really want to make it work.</p></font>

<font size="3"><b><a name="44">Raid Attendance</a></b>:</font><br>
<FONT class=Courier10 face="Courier New, adobe-courier, Courier" size=2>
<p>I think first of all I should make something very clear. The purpose of all of this work we have been doing is to try and make things fair to everyone in Fury's Edge. Whether you are EST / MST / Overseas, play 40 hours a week, play 10 hours a week we want everyone to be dedicated to pushing the guild further in what we do.</p>

<p>We also want to see people rewarded based solely on there dedication / attitude to the guild. The people that put in the extra effort or at least the best effort they can should be the people that benefit.</p>

<p>Attendance points are going to be tracked by the officers and posted publicly. These points will also be used for loot distriibution (see below). We just want to know who is showing up.</p>

<b><font size="3"><a name="45">Notes</a></b>:</font><br>
<FONT class=Courier10 face="Courier New, adobe-courier, Courier" size=2>
If it becomes apparent that you are not showing up for raids, not helping the guild in general or not supporting the system, you will be warned and the end result may be guildremoval.</font><br>

<br><hr align="CENTER" size="2" width="80%" noshade><br>

<b><font size="3"><a name="50">Alts</a></b>:</font><br><br>

<FONT class=Courier10 face="Courier New, adobe-courier, Courier" size=2>
<p>Alts are by no means meant to take priority over a Main Character.  A few restrictive measures are in place to ensure this:</p>

 - 1 Alt per Member<br>
 - Point Pool based off Main Character only.<br>
 - Admission Period will be 3 months in the guild prior to adding an alt (Not applicable for guild formation)<br><br></font>

<b><font size="3">Switching Alts / Status</b>:</font><br><br>
<FONT class=Courier10 face="Courier New, adobe-courier, Courier" size=2>
<i>Exchanging Alts</i> - De-guild current Alt in witness of a Recruiting Officer.  New Alt guilded by a Recruiting Officer.  3 month wait to exchange a new Alt.<br><br>
<i>Exchanging Alts for Mains</i> - Done during Ranking Review.  Approved only after Officer discussion.<br><br></font>

